ZH: 明天是国庆节，我们会去看阅兵式。
EN: Tomorrow is National Day, we will go watch the military parade.

ZH: 春节是中国最重要的传统节日之一。
EN: The Spring Festival is one of the most important traditional festivals in China.

ZH: 中秋节这天，我们会吃月饼并赏月。
EN: On the day of Mid-Autumn Festival, we will eat mooncakes and enjoy the moon.

ZH: 元宵节是春节结束后的第一个节日。
EN: Lantern Festival is the first festival after the Chinese New Year.

ZH: 今天是母亲节，我要给妈妈送一份礼物。
EN: Today is Mother's Day, I want to give my mom a gift.

ZH: 在万圣节，孩子们喜欢穿着各种恐怖的服装去讨糖果。
EN: On Halloween, children like to wear various scary costumes to trick-or-treat.

ZH: 情人节快到了，我打算给我女朋友买束玫瑰花。
EN: Valentine's Day is coming, I plan to buy a bouquet of roses for my girlfriend.

ZH: 教师节这天，学生们会表达对老师的感激之情。
EN: On Teacher's Day, students will express their gratitude to their teachers.

ZH: 圣诞节是西方人庆祝的重要节日。
EN: Christmas is an important festival celebrated by Westerners.

ZH: 阴历的端午节通常是在6月份。
EN: The lunar Dragon Boat Festival is usually in June.

ZH: 每个传统节日都有自己独特的庆祝方式。
EN: Each traditional festival has its own unique way of celebration.

ZH: 过节时，家人团聚是最重要的。
EN: Reuniting with family is the most important part of the festival.

ZH: 在新年的时候，我们会拜访亲朋好友。
EN: During the New Year, we will visit relatives and friends.

ZH: 除夕夜，家家户户会团聚吃年夜饭。
EN: On New Year's Eve, families will reunite to have a grand dinner.

ZH: 许多节日都和传统习俗有关。
EN: Many festivals are related to traditional customs.

ZH: 假日是放松和休息的好时机。
EN: Holidays are a good time to relax and rest.

ZH: 不同的节日有不同的象征和意义。
EN: Different festivals have different symbols and meanings.

ZH: 节日不仅仅是庆祝，更是文化传承。
EN: Festivals are not only for celebration, but also for cultural inheritance.

ZH: 过节时，人们会穿着喜庆的服装。
EN: During festivals, people will wear festive clothing.

ZH: 在节日期间，市场上总是充满了人气。
EN: During festivals, the market is always bustling with people.
